This paper deals with machine learning in an adversarial environment, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of game theory in this context, which is relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper considers the issue of data corruption, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses classification and regression, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), respectively.
